On Sun, 1 Jul 2007, Alan Beck wrote:

>
> I was doing a repair to the motor to get rid of a leak, perhaps would be the
> reason for the leak?

Only way to know is to clean it well and run the bus.  If it gets oily
again you've found your leak.  If not, leave it alone, as a dent won't
affect anything.  One of my Mexican engines came with a pushrod tube
factory-dented and it has run fine.

George
